<br>
Kunark dragons were made trivial by Manaburn.  Wern't they made trivial by Luclin equipment?<br>
<br>
For a time, there was a valid concern by players about manaburn, and how multiple wizards working together could take down pretty much any single mob.<br>
<br>
The game changed, and evolved.  The ability to have skills scaled down or not work on given mobs has evolved.  Expansions are released, class power goes up, and the class balance changes.  Yet old zones never change, only new zones.<br>
<br>
<br>
What this shows is that instead of Verant/SoE going around nerfing things, they could very well just update old zones so new abilities don't make them trivial.  Fix the old zones so the mobs meet the standards of the latest expansions.  A level 60 mob from any zone should be a level 60 mob should be a level 60 mob, no matter what expansion the mob came from.  The 32k HP cap should have been removed from all original EQ and Kunark mobs.  Retune the mobs so they are the desired difficulty.  Assume that all characters will have all expansions when you tune the zones.  <br>
<br>
Once the old zones meet the standards of the current game, the AA skills COULD be properly adjusted, and no one would be able to say, &quot;But in SolB, a level 5 character can kill Nagafen solo&quot;.  That's the problem with ANY nerf, they keep trying to balance items and abilities around different expansions.  Until the difference in available power from new expansions is removed, there will always be people who whine about the abilities of other classes.  Kunark mobs will ALWAYS be underpowered for people with Velious and beyond, Velious has all but become trivial for the majority of players with the power AA skills have brought to characters.   Guilds that arn't even considered uber can take down Avatar of War at this point.  <br>
<br>
So, Manaburn, there WERE reasons to nerf it when it was done, but those reasons are no longer fully valid.  As a result, it should be brought back as a useful skill.  The 1 minute timer on it's own would be enough to keep the skill from being exploited, so what's the reason for leaving it nerfed into uselessness?<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 65 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
