However, I did encounter an &quot;abuse&quot; with Rage when it had to be camped. There was some confusion over who had the camp but the other guild had a manaburn team so they were able to take Rage over us who did not have a manaburn team. We would have been able to make the kill without manaburn but the manaburn team was able to make the kill quick and therefore get the looting rights. That was my personal experience. I also saw some posts on the eqvault on the terris-thule section with complaints about my server manaburn team.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=natanmagus>Natan Magus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1015<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 12:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Team HARMTOUCH will make us look like nuns. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeddicous>Zeddicous</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 1:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Remember Manaburn?</span><hr size=1> Howdy all,<br>
<br>
I can't speak for all servers obviously, but on my server the manaburn crews were pretty active back in the day.  It was not at all uncommon to come home from work on patch day, and after spending a little family time log on to find out the burn crews had long ago killed the targets that had popped already.  I heard it a lot from my friends that saw it.  More than one occasion I was with my guild buffing up for a kunark dragon only to personally witness the ganksquad sprint past us and burn it down.<br>
<br>
It had to be one of the more poorly designed abilities I've seem in this system.  When it came out, it was a fairly high end Luclin ability, and the best thing the wizard community find to use it for was farming old content primarily for plat.  Even the burncrew members that I spoke with would admit that they never used Manaburn on a raid because they could be more effective without it.<br>
<br>
Granted they could have done a much better job adjusting it, but I can't say that I'm really surprised with what they reduced it to.  I think if they just upped the damage to a 3:1 ratio and leave the other limitations that it would be a nice tool to have.<br>
<br>
Feel free to flame away,<br>
Zedd-Outcast Wizard of the Quellious Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 352<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/11/03 1:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Remember Manaburn?</span><hr size=1> The ENTIRE problem is solved with the one minute timer.  Other than an extremely lucky crit, what target worth burning is gonna drop dead from the damage MB was able to do?<br>
